                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The permafrost aug will add 5dps.  Not a lot, but it's cool, and procing is fun.  I'd go for it.  Heck if you often group with Clerics that leave you at 89% hp, get the lifetap one (although it's rumored to get resisted a lot).  I hate when I play my Encahnter and the Cleric doesn't keep me at full health.  An Enchanter's job, just like the tank's, usually involves taking some hits for the team even when done perfectly, and we are therefore (or should be) a top healing priority.
<br />

<br />
Personally I'd like to see more casters swinging away!  It's fun!  Don't let this be a job.  Just remember to stay out of the damn riposte arc or I'll cut your toes off <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />.  It's sad when the meleeing Cleric and Enchanter are actually better at avoiding riposte than the Ranger, Monk, etc.  They were supposed to learn about this 65 levels ago!
<br />

<br />
I'm glad to see that the folks on this board do not agree with the person who posted this thread.  "Your job is to be bored."  Bah, on you, I say!
<br />

<br />
I want to melee with my Water Sprinkler of Forgiveness (2Her that I carry around for clicky Atone, even though it rarely works), just to have my 2H Blunt up for skill completeness.  But it's no fun not procing.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=619429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cedir</a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=673299" target="_blank" class="postlink">Raynboh</a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=890624" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pharroh</a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=676318" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nysaan</a>
