                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Something to keep in mind about the Yalp VI mana regen verses medding mana regen.  Yes sitting gives more mana regen if you can sit for good period of times.  The problem is if you stand up in the middle of a tick you loose the regen for that tick.  If your in a situation like a hard LDON where your having to stand up to cast alot of CH(10 seconds), avoiding sit agro and moving around alot your not getting alot of use out of medding.  I personally never med anymore because I found the steady mana regen of Yalp 6 to be better then the on and off mana regen from medding.  Also Yalp is affected by SCMR (I've tested it) so when your calculating how much mana regen Yalp gives you have to take this into account.
<br />

<br />
On Hard LDON I don't melee because I need to be more on my toes but you can bet I'm standing there yalping to keep my mana up.  To avoid the recycle time I just watch when I yalp.   I'll kick off a yalp before the mob hits the camp that why I'm ready if things go bad and have mana regen going.  If worse comes to worse DVA isn't affected by the recycle time.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
