                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd like to add my usual "remember the lower levels" caveat:  We ran into a "battle cleric" at about 30th level.  If I recall correctly, he was our only cleric and wanted to tank the mobs all the time.  Long and short is he never had mana and we were constantly on the run.  Based on that, I've always had a stigma in my mind for folks who wanted to be a self sufficient tank: battle clerics.
<br />

<br />
My opinion for the low level cleric remains, however, once a cleric gets yaulp V or better (level 56), and if the cleric can make the transition to being a good healer who also tanks the mobs, in that case the clerics job IS to tank because s/he is making the group more efficient.
<br />

<br />
It's the same reason I pull rather than the Bard when I'm on LDoNs.  My DPS is pitiful, my nukes are inefficient, just like the Cleric.  The DPS added by a bard is not insignificant, it's certainly better than mine.  Especially when added to the fact that he can sing songs to make the whole group more efficient.  Long and short is that it's more efficient for him to be tanking than for me to be sitting... despite the fact that I'm constantly running short on mana while pulling.  Basically, with me pulling, the folks who can do DPS, get to do that full time.  Note that at low levels I was taught to always sit to regain mana and let the pullers do their job... at lower levels I feel this was good advice, I feel that at higher levels it's not the most efficient way to do things and will not go back.
<br />

<br />
2 lessons in this thread:
<br />

<br />
Let folks do their own job in the most efficient way they can.  That is how the group gets to be most efficient.
<br />

<br />
Be open to new ways for a class to work.  Spells and levels modify how to most efficiently run your class and thus the paradigm for a class of 10 levels ago, may well be dated at this time... same might well be said for when we get a patch or expansion with new levels/abilities.
<br />

<br />
The real key (as has been said): have fun.  It's supposed to be a game.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />GnarliAnna
<br />
64 Enchanter of Silent Watchers
<br />
Cazic-Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
