                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have a cleric. I melee when I'm doing alright on mana. Like was mentioned, a cleric isn't losing 7mana per tick, they're gaining 7 less per tick. BIG difference. People seem to think that clerics should always have like 90% mana all the time. They should be sitting all the time. The only time they can stand is when they heal. This is not how a cleric should be played. In groups when I play my cleric, (she's 56 atm) I am puller most of the time. I heal, and I melee. I do ALL THREE of these things, and can still maintain my mana with kei at around 50-60%. This is with contributing a nuke every once in a while as well.
